author: poojaranjan
content:
<@494908382889639977>  EIP Editors do not prioritize EIPs in order to push it towards `Final`.  You may follow Do's and Don'ts for Editors here - https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-5069 

The present EIP process is authors' driven. 
If an EIP author is incorporating comments suggested by editors/community and generally sticks around to promote EIPs, the proposal will become a standard for Ethereum ecosystem.  

So there may not be a list of top 10-15. However, IMO actual deployments data for proposals in `Last Call` maybe value adding for authors as well as EIP editors.
